The paper deals with the Hospitals/Residents problem, which is a well-known problem in game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The concept of envy-free matching is related to fair division (cs.DM) and social choice theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the complexity of deciding the existence of an envy-free matching, which is a common topic in theoretical computer science (cs.THE) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper considers a specific model of the Hospitals/Residents problem, which involves quotas on subsets of doctors, and this is a topic in optimization (cs.OH) and social choice theory (cs.GT).
